ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Absolutely not. Unfortunately, it's mandatory for graduate BME students. This MUST be changed ASAP.
Provides a good overview of current imaging research and imaging tools. Only necessary if you work in an imaging lab or use the imaging technology.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This class had a negative impact on my area of research. My understanding of MR physics deteriorated after this class, and I have little (if any) added knowledge in MRS, PET, or FRET.This class MUST be cancelled, or at least made OPTIONAL to BME graduate students.
I learned the basics of various imaging modalities but would need to learn more on my own to determine if they could be used in my own research.
